#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:48
msgid "Lafka — Analytics"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:49
msgid "Multi-platform tracking via Google Tag Manager (orchestrator) plus direct platform fallbacks for GA4, Microsoft Clarity, and Meta Pixel. Consent Mode v2 defaults emit BEFORE any tag fires so the site is CPPA/GDPR-compliant out of the box. Paste your IDs once here — the plugin handles emit order, escaping, and consent gating."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:223
msgid "Tag manager"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:224
msgid "Google Tag Manager is the recommended orchestrator. Once GTM is set, you wire GA4 / Clarity / Meta Pixel inside the GTM UI and the plugin emits a single container snippet. The direct-platform fields below are only used when this field is empty (operator can pick the simpler path during early setup)."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:241
msgid "GTM Container ID"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:242
msgid "Format: GTM-XXXXXXX. Find it at tagmanager.google.com → your container → top-right. When set, the plugin emits the GTM head snippet + body noscript iframe per Google's install spec. Leave blank to use direct-platform IDs below."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:260
msgid "Direct platform IDs (used only if GTM is empty)"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:261
msgid "Override-not-additive: if any GTM Container ID is set above, the plugin emits ONLY the GTM snippet and lets you wire these platforms via GTM tags (avoids double-firing). GA4 has a hard cap of 500 distinct event names per property — Microsoft Clarity is unlimited and complements GA4 for heatmaps + session replay. Meta Pixel is required only if you run paid Facebook/Instagram ads. GSC verification turns on the data feed for Google Search Console (rank tracking + click metrics)."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:278
msgid "GA4 Measurement ID"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:279
msgid "Format: G-XXXXXXXXXX. Find it at analytics.google.com → Admin → Data Streams → Web → Measurement ID. Only used when GTM is empty."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:299
msgid "Microsoft Clarity Project ID"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:300
msgid "Alphanumeric project ID from clarity.microsoft.com. Free, unlimited heatmaps + session replay — complements GA4. Only used when GTM is empty."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:317
msgid "Cloudflare Web Analytics token"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:318
msgid "32-character token from dash.cloudflare.com → Analytics & Logs → Web Analytics → your site → \"JS snippet\" (the data-cf-beacon token). Cookieless + privacy-first, so it emits independently of GTM and consent."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:338
msgid "Meta Pixel ID"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:339
msgid "15-16 digit numeric ID from business.facebook.com → Events Manager → Data Sources. Only needed when running paid Facebook / Instagram ads. Only used when GTM is empty."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:356
msgid "Google Search Console verification token"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:357
msgid "Paste only the content=\"...\" value from the HTML verification snippet Google gave you (not the full meta tag). Required once to claim the property in search.google.com/search-console — after verification you can leave it set or remove it."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:372
msgid "Consent + privacy"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:373
msgid "Google Consent Mode v2 defaults emit BEFORE any tag fires so the site is compliant from the first byte. The banner appears at the bottom of the viewport until the visitor Accepts, Rejects, or sets per-category preferences. Defaults are denied (most-restrictive) — set to granted only if your legal review allows opt-out-rather-than-opt-in (some EU jurisdictions do not)."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:390
msgid "Show consent banner"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:391
msgid "When ON, the banner appears for every new visitor until they decide. When OFF, the plugin still emits the Consent Mode v2 default state (still safer than no consent at all) but never asks for an explicit decision."
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:398
msgid "Denied (most-restrictive default)"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:399
msgid "Granted (opt-out flow — check your jurisdiction first)"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:404
msgid "Default state: analytics_storage"
msgstr ""

#: incl/customizer/class-lafka-customizer-analytics.php:405
msgid "GA4 / Clarity / behavioural-analytics storage. Required for any usage metric. Defaults to denied (Consent Mode v2 baseline)."
